caption: I love the food at Brugger's, however, I know many employees who work at this specific location and I can tell that they are treated very poorly. Brugger's cares more about sales than the health and safety of their employees. Their employees are taken for granted and that creates a very hostile work environment. I will not be supporting this business as long as this behavior continues.

Disappointing! I’ve been here numerous times and have ordered single bagels, breakfast sandwiches, and coffee and have had all of these things messed up almost half of the time! Some of the staff do a great job, however many others seems extremely uninterested in doing their job properly. I’ve had lattes with no espresso (yup, just milk), been glared at for taking back a breakfast sandwich that wasn’t supposed to have cheese on it, but did (sorry, I can’t have cheese!), and been given the eye-roll for coming in 20 (yes, twenty!) minutes before close as if I was coming in with 30 seconds to spare. When they don’t mess up, the coffee and bagels are pretty delicious.

The place is nice, warm and welcoming. No line (11am), service was great. Coffee was above average. The food was served quickly. The bagel sandwiches had too much mayo (Crispy chicken) and cream cheese (cream cheese bagel). The bagels themselves were good. Bottom line - not the best breakfast in town.

The bagels weren't good and they don't even warm them up or ask if we wanted them warmed. Plus they added way too much cream cheese. They are overpriced and the Carmel macchiato I order was disgusting and almost $5 for one smaller than what I get at Starbucks.

Used to come here multiple times a week for a while, about a year and a half/two years ago. Service has seemed to gone down since then, and the shop seems understaffed so there will be some waiting time. In January 2017 alone, I came in on multiple occasions to find staff behind the counter taking care of nasty cleaning duties during the middle of customer orders - even after they put their food prep gloves on! I'm not a stickler about, for example, a piece of cheese touching the counter then going back in a sandwich; but handling cleaning chemicals and then immediately putting together a sandwich afterwards is a big no-no. I won't be coming back to this location because I think that's quite unsafe.  The bagels and sandwiches taste like how they did when I first started coming in, and the facility is pretty well-kept; +2 stars. -3 stars for the quality of service, improper training/management for the sandwich makers, and potentially serving unsafe food.

Come for the bagels.  A lot of other reviewers have spoken about the other options here, but I only come for the bagels and for that, Bruegger's get a full 5 stars.  I love the displays and the bulk purchase discounts/deals. Great selection of options, and the bagels were very fresh.  Haven't tried the other sandwich options, but I probably never will (I'm the kind of person who only gets drip coffee at Starbucks - used to be a barista and have tried everything before - I stick to what a place is best at).  Bought the baker's dozen bagel deal - got every bagel I wanted. Tried the bacon scallion (great stuff), and the lite cream cheese.

My family is half polish, so I know what a true bagel is supposed to taste like. They claim to have "New York City" bagels, which were actually first brought to the U.S by Polish-Jewish immigrants, and I've savored the taste of those as well. These are an absolute disgrace to the NYC claim, and should not label them as such. The bagels are tougher than nails, and quite honestly saw a kid lose a tooth from one the other day. Let's not even talk about service. Woof! You might as well call the place Rude-rs bagels instead. If I wanted to be treated like a piece of trash, I would have attended Trump rally wearing a Bernie shirt. Barring any unforeseen incident, I won't be going back.
